text: Ganzert is a village in the Dutch province of Gelderland. It is a part of the municipality of Buren, and lies about 8 km southwest of Veenendaal. The statistical area "Ganzert", which also can include the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 210.Statistics Netherlands (CBS), Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005.
